{"id":"f95e58eaa6a6d7ac02f84193b485471f0cd14de6","axis":"silent","repo":"withastro/astro","sha":"f95e58eaa6a6d7ac02f84193b485471f0cd14de6","parsed":{"files":[{"path":".changeset/stable-route-caching.md","lines":["@@ -0,0 +1,35 @@","+---","+'astro': minor","+---","+","+Stabilizes route caching, removing the `experimental.cache` and `experimental.routeRules` flags and replacing them with the top-level `cache` and `routeRules` configuration options.","+","+Route caching, introduced experimentally in v6.0.0, is now stable. It gives you a platform-agnostic way to cache responses from [on-demand rendered](https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/on-demand-rendering/) pages and endpoints, based on standard HTTP caching semantics.","+","+Update your config to move `cache` and `routeRules` out of the `experimental` block:","+","+```diff","+// astro.config.mjs","+import { defineConfig, memoryCache } from 'astro/config';","+","+export default defineConfig({","+-  experimental: {","+-    cache: {","+-      provider: memoryCache(),","+-    },","+-    routeRules: {","+-      '/blog/[...path]': { maxAge: 300, swr: 60 },","+-    },","+-  },","++  cache: {","++    provider: memoryCache(),","++  },","++  routeRules: {","++    '/blog/[...path]': { maxAge: 300, swr: 60 },","++  },","+});","+```","+","+Set caching directives in your routes with `Astro.cache` (in `.astro` pages) or `context.cache` (in API routes and middleware), and Astro translates them into the appropriate headers or runtime behavior depending on your configured cache provider. You can also define cache rules for routes declaratively in your config using `routeRules`, without modifying route code.","+","+See the [route caching guide](https://docs.astro.build/en/guides/caching/) for more information."],"additions":35,"deletions":0,"truncated":false},{"path":"packages/astro/src/core/build/plugins/plugin-manifest.ts","lines":["@@ -390,10 +390,7 @@ async function buildManifest("," \t\tallowedDomains: settings.config.security?.allowedDomains,"," \t\tkey: encodedKey,"," \t\tsessionConfig: sessionConfigToManifest(settings.config.session),","-\t\tcacheConfig: cacheConfigToManifest(","-\t\t\tsettings.config.experimental?.cache,","-\t\t\tsettings.config.experimental?.routeRules,","-\t\t),","+\t\tcacheConfig: cacheConfigToManifest(settings.config.cache, settings.config.routeRules),"," \t\tcsp,"," \t\timage: {"," \t\t\tobjectFit: settings.config.image.objectFit,"],"additions":1,"deletions":4,"truncated":false},{"path":"packages/astro/src/core/cache/config.ts","lines":["@@ -16,8 +16,8 @@ const CacheOptionsSchema = z.object({"," });"," "," /**","- * Cache provider configuration (experimental.cache).","- * Provider only - routes are configured via experimental.routeRules.","+ * Cache provider configuration (`cache`).","+ * Provider only - routes are configured via `routeRules`.","  */"," export const CacheSchema = z.object({"," \tprovider: CacheProviderConfigSchema.optional(),","@@ -26,14 +26,15 @@ export const CacheSchema = z.object({"," const RouteRuleSchema = CacheOptionsSchema;"," "," /**","- * Route rules configuration (experimental.routeRules).","- * Maps glob patterns to route rules.","+ * Route rules configuration (`routeRules`).","+ * Maps route patterns to route rules. Patterns use the same `[param]` and","+ * `[...rest]` syntax as file-based routing; glob wildcards (`*`) are not supported.","  *","  * Example:","  * ```ts","  * routeRules: {","- *   '/api/*': { swr: 600 },","- *   '/products/*': { maxAge: 3600, tags: ['products'] },","+ *   '/api/[...path]': { swr: 600 },","+ *   '/products/[...slug]': { maxAge: 3600, tags: ['products'] },","  * }","  * ```","  */"],"additions":7,"deletions":6,"truncated":false},{"path":"packages/astro/src/core/cache/runtime/noop.ts","lines":["@@ -49,7 +49,7 @@ export class DisabledAstroCache implements CacheLike {"," \t\t\thasWarned = true;"," \t\t\tthis.#logger?.warn("," \t\t\t\t'cache',","-\t\t\t\t'`cache.set()` was called but caching is not enabled. Co